      "created": "2022-03-23T14:07:29.889+0000",
      "description": "Node load based scheduler is quite effective for cluster stability, epecially when we deploy NodeManager, DataNode and use Auxservices like mapreduce shuffle or spark shuffle.\r\n\r\nWe can set up threshold and auto skip the nodes with high load when scheduling.\r\nNode load should mainly focus on CPU, Memory and DiskIO.\r\n\r\nKeeping CPU and Memory under a healthy threshold makes container and task time more stable, reduces the possibility of OOM kill by OS. As for DiskIO, \r\nhigh disk load will more likely cause slow DataNode and fetch failure when shuffling data.",
